docs.lead_paragraph: CEDARHURST, L.I., July 4. -- Mrs. Rose Klafter, whose husband maintains a drapery shop at 92 Carman Avenue here, said last night that she had not heard from her brother, Samuel Lehrmann, for months. He left his home in Corona for California in January, she said, on a trip for his health and with the intention of seeking employment on the West Coast.
docs.abstract: Hibbick, M, rescued after elevator falls
